2 . mains 


📝 STAGE 2: UPSC Mains Examination (Descriptive Type)
Total of 9 Papers | Total Marks (for merit): 1750
Duration per paper: 3 hours

📜 Qualifying Papers (Need 25% marks to qualify – marks not counted in merit)
✅ Paper A: Indian Language (300 marks)
Choose one from the 22 languages in the 8th Schedule of the Constitution (e.g., Hindi, Tamil, Bengali, Telugu, Urdu, etc.)

Essay writing, comprehension, translation (English ↔ Language), grammar & vocabulary

✅ Paper B: English (300 marks)
Similar structure: essay, précis, comprehension, grammar, usage

🧠 Papers Counted for Final Merit (1750 Marks Total)
🔹 Paper I: Essay (250 Marks)
2 sections with 4 topics each — choose 1 essay from each section

Topics may be philosophical, societal, political, environmental, etc.

Assessed for:

Logical structure

Clarity of thought

Originality

Coherence and relevance

🔹 Paper II: General Studies I (250 Marks)
🏛️ Indian Heritage & Culture
Art forms, literature, architecture

📜 History
Modern Indian history (freedom struggle, personalities, events)

Post-independence consolidation

World history (18th century onwards – revolutions, world wars)

🌍 Geography
Physical geography (earthquakes, volcanoes, climatology)

Human geography

Resource distribution

Geographical features and their location (India & world)

🔹 Paper III: General Studies II (250 Marks)
⚖️ Polity and Constitution
Features of the Constitution

Federalism, devolution of powers

Functions/responsibilities of the Union & States

🏛️ Governance
Government policies & interventions

Role of civil services

⚖️ Social Justice
Welfare schemes, health, education, vulnerable sections

🌐 International Relations
Bilateral, regional and global groupings

India's neighborhood

Effect of foreign policies on Indian interests

🔹 Paper IV: General Studies III (250 Marks)
💹 Economy
Inclusive growth and budgeting

Agriculture and food processing

Infrastructure (energy, ports, roads, airports)

🧪 Science and Technology
Awareness in IT, robotics, nanotech, biotech, AI, etc.

🌱 Environment and Ecology
Conservation, pollution, climate change, wildlife

🔐 Security & Disaster Management
Internal security challenges

Role of security agencies

Disaster management basics

🔹 Paper V: General Studies IV (250 Marks)
🧭 Ethics, Integrity, and Aptitude
Ethics and Human Interface

Attitude, emotional intelligence

Civil service values: integrity, impartiality, compassion

Probity in governance

Public service values and ethics

Case Studies (practical ethical dilemmas)

🔹 Papers VI & VII: Optional Subject Papers (250 marks each)
Choose ONE optional subject from UPSC list (48 subjects including literature options).

Examples:

PSIR (Political Science & IR)

Sociology

Anthropology

History

Geography

Public Administration

Philosophy

Hindi Literature, English Literature, Urdu Lit, etc.

Each subject has:

Paper I – Theoretical foundations

Paper II – Application & Indian context










🎤 STAGE 3: UPSC Personality Test / Interview (275 Marks)
Face-to-face interview held at UPSC Bhavan, New Delhi

Assesses:

Personality traits

Moral integrity

Communication

Decision-making

Knowledge of:

Optional subject

Current affairs

Graduation subjects

Hobbies

Situational & ethical judgment

🧾 Final Merit Calculation
Mains (7 merit papers): 1750 marks

Interview: 275 marks

✅ Total: 2025 marks

📚 Top Resources for Mains Preparation
NCERTs (Class 6–12) – all subjects

Standard Books:

Polity: M. Laxmikanth

History: Spectrum, Bipin Chandra

Geography: GC Leong, NCERTs

Economy: Ramesh Singh, Budget/Eco Survey

Ethics: Lexicon, Subba Rao

Current Affairs:

The Hindu / Indian Express

Yojana, Kurukshetra

PIB, Rajya Sabha TV Debates

Answer Writing Practice:

Vision IAS, ForumIAS, Insights Test Series

🔧 Available Formats (let me know what you need):
📄 Printable PDF (organized like this)

🌐 HTML/Web page format

📆 Weekly Study Plan

📋 Excel or Google Sheets format (subject-wise syllabus)






