<body>
    <header>
        <h1>UPSC Interview (Personality Test) Details</h1>
    </header>

    <div class="container">
        <div class="section">
            <h2>1. What is the UPSC Interview?</h2>
            <p>The UPSC Interview, officially called the Personality Test, is the third and final stage of the Civil Services Examination (CSE) conducted by the Union Public Service Commission (UPSC). It is designed to assess a candidate's personality and suitability for a career in the civil services.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>2. Purpose of the Interview</h2>
            <p>The interview assesses the personality of candidates, including qualities like clarity of expression, confidence, leadership ability, social awareness, and more. It's not about what you know but who you are.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>3. Interview Marks and Weightage</h2>
            <p>The interview carries a total of 275 marks, and the final merit is based on a total of 2025 marks (1750 for Mains + 275 for the Interview).</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>4. Common Interview Questions</h2>
            <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFAQ('faq1')">
                What kind of questions are asked in the UPSC Interview?
            </div>
            <div class="faq-answer" id="faq1">
                <p>Common questions include personal introduction, academic background, current affairs, and opinions on important national and international issues. Panelists may also ask about your hobbies and DAF (Detailed Application Form).</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>5. Tips from Toppers</h2>
            <p>Stay calm, be authentic, and focus on your personality and communication. Know your DAF inside out and stay updated with current affairs.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>6. Dress Code for Interview Day</h2>
            <p>Men: Formal shirt, trousers, shoes; blazer or tie optional. Women: Saree or formal Indian wear, or western formals. Appearance should be neat and professional.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <footer>
        <p>Best of Luck with your UPSC preparation!</p>
    </footer>

    <script>
        function toggleFAQ(faqId) {
            var faq = document.getElementById(faqId);
            if (faq.style.display === "none" || faq.style.display === "") {
                faq.style.display = "block";
            } else {
                faq.style.display = "none";
            }
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>



